      "id": "E2-04-Q1",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 3,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "questionText": "Find the value of each of the following.\n\n(a) $27^{2/3}$ \u2003 (b) $16^{-3/4}$ \u2003 (c) $\\left(\\dfrac{4}{9}\\right)^{-1/2}$",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) 9, (b) 1/8, (c) 3/2",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$27^{2/3} = (\\sqrt[3]{27})^2 = 3^2 = 9$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$16^{-3/4} = \\dfrac{1}{(\\sqrt[4]{16})^3} = \\dfrac{1}{2^3} = \\dfrac{1}{8}$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "$\\left(\\dfrac{4}{9}\\right)^{-1/2} = \\left(\\dfrac{9}{4}\\right)^{1/2} = \\dfrac{3}{2}$" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $27^{2/3} = (27^{1/3})^2 = 3^2 = 9$",
        "(b) $16^{-3/4} = \\dfrac{1}{16^{3/4}} = \\dfrac{1}{(16^{1/4})^3} = \\dfrac{1}{2^3} = \\dfrac{1}{8}$",
        "(c) $\\left(\\dfrac{4}{9}\\right)^{-1/2} = \\left(\\dfrac{9}{4}\\right)^{1/2} = \\dfrac{\\sqrt{9}}{\\sqrt{4}} = \\dfrac{3}{2}$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Use the rule $a^{m/n} = (\\sqrt[n]{a})^m$; for negative indices, take the reciprocal first."
    },
